Even by pre-season standards, Moussa Sissoko had endured a torrid afternoon.

Invariably he had passed it to an opposition jersey or, worse still, straight out of play.

But following a sedate 88 minutes, it was he who sparked life into this most turgid affair.

Gabriel Obertan attacked the by-line and drew back to the edge of the area where Sissoko was lurking.

