Given how he had performed until that point, fans in the Gallowgate End would have been forgiven had they ducked for cover.

But the France international kept his composure and produced the game's one moment of quality, tucking into the bottom corner to win the game for his side.

It was United's final friendly of the summer but manager Alan Pardew would have taken little from it.

In the 10th minute Daryl Janmaat escaped down the right but his low cross skipped off the greasy surface and into the arms of Geronimo Rulli with Emmanuel Riviere sliding in.

The best chance of the opening exchanges came the way of the visitors when Inigo Martinez split the back four to spring Imanol Agirretxe clear. The striker, however, tried to be too cute and his chip was easily gathered by Tim Krul.

