And that was as close as either side came during a subdued first half.

Pardew introduced Rolando Aarons during the break and his arrival triggered an improvement in tempo.

Jack Colback swapped passes with Riviere and burst into the area only to see his low drive blocked by a sliding Markel Bergara.

Aarons then escaped three defenders but, with options left and right, elected to shoot and scuffed tamely into the arms of Rulli.

The Sociedad stopper was again called into action on the hour mark, producing an instinctive one-handed save to deny Mike Williamson after he had headed towards the top corner from Remy Cabella's corner.

And so it was left to Sissoko to win it after fine work from Obertan. Thankfully, the full-time whistle sounded soon after. Competitive action cannot come quickly enough.

